   Cristina Berm&lt;U+00FA&gt;dez1 (pronunciation: [kristina be&lt;U+027E&gt;mude&lt;U+03B8&gt;]) was a Princess of Le&lt;U+00F3&gt;n and Galicia. She is also known as Cristina de Le&lt;U+00F3&gt;n.2
Biography
Cristina was a daughter of King Bermudo II the Gouty and his first wife, Queen Velasquita Ram&lt;U+00ED&gt;rez.345
Her grandparents were King Ordo&lt;U+00F1&gt;o III of Le&lt;U+00F3&gt;n
Rodr&lt;U+00ED&gt;guez Fern&lt;U+00E1&gt;ndez, Justiniano: Ordo&lt;U+00F1&gt;o III Ediciones Leonesas, S.A.(1982) ISBN 84-86013-04-6 and Queen Urraca Fern&lt;U+00E1&gt;ndez.6
Cristina&lt;U+2019&gt;s stepmother was Elvira Garc&lt;U+00ED&gt;a and her half-siblings were Alfonso the Noble, Teresa and Sancha.7 She was an aunt of Princess Sancha of Le&lt;U+00F3&gt;n.
In 1010, Cristina married Prince Ordo&lt;U+00F1&gt;o Ram&lt;U+00ED&gt;rez, son of Ramiro III of Le&lt;U+00F3&gt;n8 and Sancha G&lt;U+00F3&gt;mez. They had children:
Don Alfonso Ord&lt;U+00F3&gt;&lt;U+00F1&gt;ez, who had a daughter called Cristina
Do&lt;U+00F1&gt;a Aldonza Ord&lt;U+00F3&gt;&lt;U+00F1&gt;ez, wife of Don Pelayo Froilaz
Don Ordo&lt;U+00F1&gt;o Ord&lt;U+00F3&gt;&lt;U+00F1&gt;ez, named after his father
Do&lt;U+00F1&gt;a Pelaya Ord&lt;U+00F3&gt;&lt;U+00F1&gt;ez910
After her husband died, Cristina become a nun and lived in Monasterio de San Salvador.
